title: return_position_impl_trait_in_trait compiler bug

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Stumbled across this compiler panic and replicated it with this. Likely related to the match statement. ### Code EDIT: A smaller example here: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=b35b23433ea143234d37f0e528fe559e https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=f84b78cc8ef056b4cc2029784ef6f65d ```Rust #![feature(return_position_impl_trait_in_trait)] struct TestA {} struct TestB {} impl TestTrait for TestA { type Output = (); } impl TestTrait for TestB { type Output = (); } trait TestTrait { type Output; } impl TestTrait for GreeterOutput where A: TestTrait, B: TestTrait, { type Output = (); } enum GreeterOutput where A: TestTrait, B: TestTrait, { SayHello(A), SayGoodbye(B), } trait Greeter { fn test_func(&self, func: &str) -> impl TestTrait { match func { "SayHello" => GreeterOutput::SayHello(TestA {}), "SayGoodbye" => GreeterOutput::SayGoodbye(TestB {}), _ => GreeterOutput::SayHello(TestA {}), } } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.0-nightly (9c07efe84 2022-12-16) binary: rustc commit-hash: 9c07efe84f28a44f3044237696acc295aa407ee5 commit-date: 2022-12-16 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output
